  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dbb \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0daf\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Three people who attacked the houses of MPs are in the net",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The police headquarters says that three suspects have been arrested in connection with the attack on the homes and offices of parliamentarians Milan Jayathilaka, Lasantha Alagiyawanna and Arunditha Fernando on May 09 and causing damage and looting of property.",
        "The police headquarters said that they were arrested in the areas of Kiridivela and Dankotuwa, and that they were arrested yesterday (27) evening by the Western South Crime Division and Dankotuwa police.",
        "According to the police headquarters, they have been arrested in the areas of Mr. Milan Jayathilaka and Lasanna Alagiyawanna in Kiridiwela and Dankotuwa of Mr. Arunditha Fernando under the charges of attacking properties including houses and offices.",
        "During the country-wide violence after the attack on the protestors in front of the Galumudora and Araliyagaha mansions on the 9th of May last, the homes and properties of a large number of Parliamentary Ministers were attacked and destroyed by angry mobs."
      ],
